# Project context

- If `.env` or `MASTER_CONTEXT.md` do not exist, tell the user to run `./scripts/setup.sh`.
- At the **start** of substantive work in this repo, read **MASTER_CONTEXT.md** at the repository root for brand voice, cost rates, preferred image host, and API learnings.
- If `MASTER_CONTEXT.md` has empty fields (cost rates, preferred host, brand voice), offer to populate them — ask the user and write the values back.
- After **significant** changes (new workflows, verified kie.ai behaviors, brand updates), append a short **dated** entry to the Changelog section in **MASTER_CONTEXT.md**.
- For kie.ai HTTP usage, prompts, and polling, follow **`.cursor/skills/kie-ai-external-api/SKILL.md`** and linked **reference.md**.
